## ðŸ”Œ Circuit Connections

### Arduino UNO
| Arduino Pin | Connected To | Description |
|--------------|--------------|--------------|
| D2 | DHT11 Data | Sensor input |
| D3 | PIR Output | Motion detection |
| D7 | Relay IN1 | Light control |
| D8 | Relay IN2 | Fan control |
| A4 | LCD SDA | IÂ²C data line |
| A5 | LCD SCL | IÂ²C clock line |
| 5V | VCC of DHT11, PIR, Relay, LCD | Power |
| GND | All module GNDs | Common ground |

### ESP8266 (Wi-Fi Module)
| ESP Pin | Connection | Notes |
|----------|-------------|-------|
| RX | Arduino TX (through voltage divider) | 3.3 V logic |
| TX | Arduino RX | Direct connection |
| VCC | 3.3 V | Power supply |
| GND | Common ground | |
| CH_PD | 3.3 V | Enable Wi-Fi chip |

> âš ï¸ **Use a voltage divider (1.8 kÎ© + 3.3 kÎ©)** for Arduino TX â†’ ESP RX line.  
> Do **not** power the ESP8266 from Arduino 3.3 V for long periods â€” use NodeMCU USB or external 3.3 V regulator.

---

## ðŸ§  System Workflow
1. **DHT11** measures temperature and humidity.  
2. **PIR sensor** detects room occupancy.  
3. **Arduino** decides whether to turn lights/fans ON/OFF using the relay.  
4. **LCD** shows real-time values.  
5. **ESP8266** uploads sensor data to the cloud (ThingSpeak/Blynk).  

